# Rule: scripts/README.md

Documents the boundary between `scripts/` and `packages/`. The rule
itself is short:

- `scripts/` is **repo-root tooling** — `check-md`, `check-files`,
  `reindex-memory`, and similar one-shot checks that operate on the
  whole repo;
- `scripts/_scratch/` (gitignored) is for throwaway helpers;
- product logic does **not** live in `scripts/`; if a script grows
  past ~100 lines of meaningful code, it deserves its own
  `packages/<name>/` and a `package.json` of its own.

## Template

```markdown
# `scripts/` — repo-root tooling

> **What lives here.** Small one-shot helpers that operate on the
> whole repo…

## Layout

- `check-md.ts` — enforces the `.md` rule.
- `check-files.ts` — enforces sibling-README under `packages/`.
- `reindex-memory.ts` — emits `.agents/memory/index.tsv`.
- `_scratch/` (gitignored) — throwaway helpers.

## What does NOT live here

Product logic. If a script outgrows this folder, it becomes
`packages/<name>/`.
```
